<p>24 July 1915<br/>Saturday</p>
<p>At work this morning from 5 am to 9 am.<br/>Carrying pipes   &amp;  laying them<br/>On again from midnight to 2.15 am then "Stand to" until 4 am until the Moon sets<br/>This job is permanent until further notice<br/>Rum issue at 6 pm</p>
<p>1915 July 25<br/>Sunday<br/>8th After Trinity</p>
<p>Great doings in camp our Brigadier has been promoted to Brigadier General John Monash<br/>Usual midnight job but not hard work this time</p>
